00:05:08.070 --> 00:05:13.630
The biggest challenge for me
is to hold the confidence,
not to be

00:05:13.630 --> 00:05:16.590
disturbed by what a clown
ought to be.

00:05:17.900 --> 00:05:21.270
You need a certain costume,
but it's not enough.

00:05:22.040 --> 00:05:27.500
You have to have
a certain state of being,
a certain state of innocence.

00:05:27.500 --> 00:05:30.910
[♪ music ♪]

00:05:30.910 --> 00:05:34.540
The clown is
the master of failure.

00:05:34.690 --> 00:05:38.870
He loves the fiasco;
he's going into
one fiasco to the other.

00:05:40.440 --> 00:05:44.350
And when you want
to do something funny,
it's most of the time
it's not funny.

00:05:45.620 --> 00:05:48.020
But when you wait,
something happens.

00:05:48.020 --> 00:05:51.590
[♪ music ♪]

00:05:51.590 --> 00:05:56.560
And when I'm a good clown
everybody can take
something from it.

00:05:56.560 --> 00:06:30.720
[♪ music ♪]

00:06:30.720 --> 00:06:36.110
Everything is important,
but nothing is
really very serious.

00:06:37.640 --> 00:06:41.400
When these two come together,
not to take everything important

00:06:41.400 --> 00:06:47.780
and nothing serious—
this is really—wow—
that's really something.

